4
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:08,400
My mom is up for parole,

5
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,000
and I'm trying
to help her get out.

6
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:13,170
I just didn't want you to think
I was blowing you off.

7
00:00:13,180 --> 00:00:14,210
You don't have to worry.

8
00:00:14,210 --> 00:00:15,340
I'm not gonna tell
anybody at work.

9
00:00:15,340 --> 00:00:17,750
This is our thing.
Nobody else's.

10
00:00:17,750 --> 00:00:19,780
You don't get to come back,

11
00:00:19,780 --> 00:00:22,450
married and pregnant,
saying that you miss me.

12
00:00:22,450 --> 00:00:24,120
You walked away.

13
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:30,420
- Did you start that fire?
- I didn't do anything wrong.

14
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:32,390
Who the hell are you?

15
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,260
What are you doing
with Ernie?

16
00:00:34,260 --> 00:00:35,600
I said, what are you
doing with that kid?

17
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:38,430
I've never seen anyone
return to full duty

18
00:00:38,430 --> 00:00:40,400
- after this surgery.
- Rene, she's transferring

19
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:43,400
to Madrid for her job
and found a great rehab unit.

20
00:00:43,410 --> 00:00:47,170
- How long you staying?
- I'm moving there.

21
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:48,510
[elevator dings]

22
00:00:52,810 --> 00:00:56,550
Oh. [laughs]

23
00:00:56,550 --> 00:00:58,550
No. No, no, no,
no, no, no.

24
00:00:58,550 --> 00:01:00,820
- Come on.
- No!

25
00:01:00,820 --> 00:01:03,290
Wow.

26
00:01:03,290 --> 00:01:05,360
Do you mind
taking our picture?

27
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:07,760
Sure.

28
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:10,130
[laughs]

29
00:01:10,130 --> 00:01:13,430
Apartment fire.
Ten-car pile up.

30
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:15,140
- Hand caught in a machine.
- Okay, all right.

31
00:01:15,140 --> 00:01:17,540
In Madrid,
it is going to be,

32
00:01:17,540 --> 00:01:21,340
um, tapas, tapas,
dance club,

33
00:01:21,340 --> 00:01:23,610
and, um,
Catholic church.

34
00:01:23,610 --> 00:01:25,350
You think I can dance?

35
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:28,420
Well, I can dance
and you can just watch.

36
00:01:28,420 --> 00:01:30,680
That, I can do.

37
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:33,320
- I've never done that before.
- Oh, yeah?

38
00:01:33,320 --> 00:01:34,320
- Yeah.
- Wow.

39
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:35,820
Well, then I guess
this is gonna be the first

40
00:01:35,830 --> 00:01:37,490
- of many new things then, huh?
- Yeah.

41
00:01:37,490 --> 00:01:39,390
Yeah.

42
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:46,730
What is it?

43
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:49,170
I met this doctor.

44
00:01:49,170 --> 00:01:51,640
- A doctor?
- Not like that.

45
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:54,440
I just, um...

46
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,340
Well, I put out
some feelers

47
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:58,510
to my medical contacts
and, um,

48
00:01:58,510 --> 00:02:01,420
it turns out that
the Chief of orthopedics

49
00:02:01,420 --> 00:02:03,150
over at River Forest Hospital

50
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:07,390
is pioneering some kind of
experimental spinal surgery,

51
00:02:07,390 --> 00:02:10,460
and he wants to meet you.

52
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:15,260
- Really?
- Yeah.

53
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,630
You know what?
Maybe this will help you

54
00:02:16,630 --> 00:02:19,630
get to Madrid even sooner.

55
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:24,670
[phone rings]

56
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:27,770
Chief Boden.

57
00:02:27,780 --> 00:02:29,740
Do you remember me?

58
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:32,380
- Ernie.
- Yeah.

59
00:02:32,380 --> 00:02:34,620
What's going on?

60
00:02:34,620 --> 00:02:36,780
You okay?

61
00:02:38,490 --> 00:02:39,520
No.

62
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:42,160
[sighs]

63
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,320
Talk to me.

64
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:46,760
Where are you?

65
00:02:48,530 --> 00:02:50,500
Ernie.

66
00:02:51,770 --> 00:02:53,900
Ernie.

67
00:02:55,170 --> 00:02:57,640
Ernie.

68
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:09,550
[siren blares]

69
00:03:09,550 --> 00:03:12,220
[horn blasting]

70
00:03:14,490 --> 00:03:17,190
Hardware store.
Not good.

71
00:03:17,190 --> 00:03:19,490
Cruz, Mills,
vent the roof.

72
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,360
Hardware store's got
propane tanks, accelerants.

73
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:24,730
[boom]

74
00:03:27,940 --> 00:03:29,440
Go, go, go!

75
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:31,340
[siren blares]

76
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:34,410
Dispatch 35,
battalion 25's on scene.

77
00:03:34,410 --> 00:03:36,540
Copy that, 25.

78
00:03:37,410 --> 00:03:39,410
Got one down.
[metal clangs]

79
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:41,980
Herrmann, take his legs.

80
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:44,420
[overlapping chatter]

81
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:56,460
- No pulse.
- Not breathing.

82
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:58,330
Fire's out, Chief.

83
00:03:58,330 --> 00:04:01,300
Looks like
another dumpster fire.

84
