2 feet off the ground.

100
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:58,630
So one time I tell
my brother nick,

101
00:04:58,630 --> 00:05:00,790
I say, "Go inside
and grab some butter."

102
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,300
- What?
- We got a rule.

103
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:04,030
You tell a story
that we've all heard

104
00:05:04,030 --> 00:05:05,970
a million times,
we raise our hand,

105
00:05:05,970 --> 00:05:07,600
you gotta shut up,
no questions asked.

106
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,440
That's actually impolite
and insulting.

107
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:10,640
Like that's on us. [laughs]

108
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:11,870
I haven't heard the story.

109
00:05:11,870 --> 00:05:13,610
Mills, let's go.

110
00:05:13,610 --> 00:05:14,810
Where are you guys going?

111
00:05:14,810 --> 00:05:16,640
Oh, I asked Cruz
to give me driving lessons.

112
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:18,780
I'm actually next in line
to drive 81.

113
00:05:18,780 --> 00:05:20,710
You know that.
Lieutenant?

114
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,320
Not now, Otis.

115
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,950
[sighs]

116
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:28,820
Hey, I... I got this dog here,
if anyone wants it.

117
00:05:28,820 --> 00:05:30,490
Don't even think about it.

118
00:05:30,490 --> 00:05:32,730
Had a dog over at 80
when I was there.

119
00:05:32,730 --> 00:05:35,400
Still have the teeth marks
in my ankle to prove it.

120
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,530
My dad says he's gonna
throw it in the river

121
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:38,800
if I don't get rid of it.

122
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:42,370
I'll take it, or at least I can find
 a home for it or something.

123
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:43,540
[dog whimpers]

124
00:05:43,540 --> 00:05:44,870
He likes bacon.

125
00:05:44,870 --> 00:05:46,910
Well, there's that.

126
00:05:46,910 --> 00:05:49,480
Does he have a name?

127
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,680
Aw, dad,
can we keep it?

128
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,820
Huh, can we?
Can we? Can we?

129
00:05:55,820 --> 00:05:57,480
Keep what?

130
00:05:57,490 --> 00:05:58,750
The dog.

131
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:01,490
[dog yipping]

132
00:06:01,490 --> 00:06:03,560
The kid's dad
was gonna drown it

133
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:06,390
- if we didn't take him.
- He can't stay.

134
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:11,370
I got a call at 67
over at Morningside.

135
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:12,970
They need relief
for the next two shifts.

136
00:06:12,970 --> 00:06:14,940
- I'll do it.
- What?

137
00:06:14,940 --> 00:06:16,700
That's the slowest house
in the city.

138
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,810
I'll do it.

139
00:06:18,810 --> 00:06:20,840
Oh, what the hell?

140
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:23,130
You've got a 
medical furlough, Severide.

141
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:24,810
That means you're medically
required to be out drinking.

142
00:06:24,810 --> 00:06:27,780
Yeah, well...

143
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:30,880
this may be more
than just a furlough.

144
00:06:32,450 --> 00:06:35,660
I'm moving to Spain
with Renee.

145
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:44,000
Between your history
with us

146
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,870
and your father's
distinguished career,

147
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:48,740
I can get you
arson investigation.

148
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:51,710
Or the academy.
Your choice.

149
00:06:51,710 --> 00:06:53,040
I appreciate it, Chief,
I do.

150
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:57,040
But I'm leaving.

151
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:59,450
Kelly...

152
00:06:59,450 --> 00:07:02,020
Just sleep on it.

153
00:07:03,890 --> 00:07:06,590
I have.

154
00:07:06,590 --> 00:07:08,020
[sighs]

155
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:10,490
Hey.

156
00:07:10,490 --> 00:07:13,060
You okay?

157
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:17,900
You were right about Ernie.

158
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:19,800
He called,
said he was in trouble,

159
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:22,570
and then he hung up.

160
00:07:22,570 --> 00:07:25,710
Right before we responded
to another dumpster fire.

161
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:30,440
I don't know where
to find him.

162
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:32,050
You tried
to help him, Chief.

163
00:07:32,050 --> 00:07:33,910
- Did I?
- You reached out to him.

164
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:36,850
You invited him in.

165
00:07:36,850 --> 00:07:42,920
Kelly, I saw him
with this man...

166
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:45,130
Everything about it
felt wrong.

167
00:07:45,130 --> 00:07:47,590
And you handed it over
to the police.

168
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,860
And what have they done, huh?
Nothing.

169
00:08:00,010 --> 00:08:02,980
Hey, I must have
misheard Cap,

170
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:06,580
because he said something
about you going to Spain.

171
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:07,880
Yeah. I was gonna
tell you this morning,

172
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:10,820
but... I missed you.

173
00:08:10,820 --> 00:08:13,250
How long
have you known this?

174
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:16,120
A day.
Maybe two.

175
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:18,890
[alarm blares]

176
00:08:18,890 --> 00:08:21,160
[over P.A.] Truck 81.
Ambulance 61.

177
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,930
425 Lake Street.

178
00:08:22,930 --> 00:08:25,070
Infant shooting.

179
00:08:30,670 --> 00:08:32,910
[engine starts]

180
00:08:32,910 --> 00:08:34,940
[siren blares]

181
00:08:34,940 --> 00:08:37,280
My baby!

182
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,810
My baby's been shot.

183
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:51,560
[cocks gun]
Baby!

184
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,690
You called the cops?

185
00:08:52,690 --> 00:08:54,560
You've been shot, baby.

186
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,700
Put down that gun.

187
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,130
- Aah!
- Whoa, take it easy.

188
00:08:58,130 --> 00:09:00,900
Shut up
and stay away from me!

189
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,170
I'm not going back to jail.

190
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:09,640
We're not the cops.

191
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:11,550
- This was self-defense.
- Of course it was.

192
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:13,010
You stay where you are.

193
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:15,320
Are you gonna shoot me
for helping your mom?

194
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:18,150
[pounding at door]
Fire department!

195
00:09:18,150 --> 00:09:20,150
[pounding]

196
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:22,790
Tell 'em to stop bangin'!
Tell 'em to stop, or I'm gonna blow a hole

197
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:24,190
right through that door!
[taser buzzes]

198
00:09:24,190 --> 00:09:25,990
Dawson? Shay?

199
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:27,260
You can't carry a taser.

200
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:30,000
Yeah, well,
tell that to baby.

201
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,870
[thud]

202
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,340
Baby here, uh,
coldcocked his mom

203
00:09:35,340 --> 00:09:38,100
and then tripped
and bumped his head.

204
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:41,910
Baby?

205
00:09:49,220 --> 00:09:51,790
Where in code of conduct book
does it say

206
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:53,320
you can't carry a taser?

207
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,020
Page one.

208
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:57,860
Oh, I should
totally read that someday.

209
00:10:01,030 --> 00:10:03,300
Hey, Otis, remember to bring
some reading materials

210
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:05,300
with you to Morningside.

211
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:07,930
Ten bucks you sell
more Morningside t-shirts

212
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,040
to tourists
than you get calls.

213
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:11,640
Wager denied.

214
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:13,970
[both laugh]

215
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:17,080
Yo, Dawson, hold up.

216
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:21,720
Yo, I'm sorry about before.

217
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,180
It's just that
on shift, it's...

218
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:25,220
Oh, stop it.
It's all right.

219
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:27,920
It's just...

220
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,890
You know that
it drives me crazy.

221
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:35,000
We'll figure it out.

222
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,400
Text me after
you get some rest.

223
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:39,170
Sounds good.

224
00:10:39,170 --> 00:10:40,630
Mm.

225
00:10:44,270 --> 00:10:47,040
[horn honks]

226
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:49,340
Do you wanna
get breakfast?

227
00:10:49,340 --> 00:10:52,410
Yeah, sure, absolutely.

228
00:11:05,390 --> 00:11:07,730
Wow, look at you.

229
00:11:07,730 --> 00:11:09,400
You look like
you're about to pop.

230
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:12,230
Yeah, a few more weeks.

231
00:11:12,230 --> 00:11:13,430
Thank you.

232
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:15,300
I heard
if you eat eggplant,

233
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:16,440
the baby comes right out.

234
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,240
I moved out.

235
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,840
What?

236
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:24,440
I told Daniel
it wasn't gonna work. Ever.

237
00:11:26,410 --> 00:11:28,420
And, I, uh...

238
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:31,120
I moved back in
with my parents.

239
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:33,350
- Wow.
- Yeah, I know.

240
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:36,390
I mean, it's exactly
where I imagined my life at 30,

241
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:38,830
back with Barb and Gene
in my room,

242
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:40,330
- with the no doubt poster.
- Right.

243
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:43,400
- Yeah.
- And don't forget pregnant.

244
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:51,140
Well, I know
what you're thinking.

245
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:52,840
What's that?

246
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:55,310
That the way I live my life
finally caught up with me.

247
00:11:55,310 --> 00:11:56,780
That's not
what I'm thinking.

248
00:11:56,780 --> 00:11:59,880
And you would be right.

249
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:03,480
Anyway, um,
I just came back

250
00:12:03,490 --> 00:12:06,290
'cause I wanted to say
thank you again.

251
00:12:06,290 --> 00:12:07,820
I mean,
you were a friend to me

252
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:10,490
when I did not deserve one.

253
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,800
Forget Gene and Barb.
Stay with me.

254
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,360
N... That's not
why I came back.

255
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:21,430
No, end of discussion.

256
00:12:24,370 --> 00:12:25,810
And you don't wanna get on

257
00:12:25,810 --> 00:12:27,370
the wrong side of my <i>abuela.</i>
Trust me.

258
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:28,940
She's got this look
that she'll throw you

259
00:12:28,940 --> 00:12:31,410
when she's aggravated.

260
00:12:31,410 --> 00:12:32,410
[both laugh]

261
00:12:32,410 --> 00:12:34,410
That means tread lightly.

262
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:37,480
Yeah, I can see that.

263
00:12:42,460 --> 00:12:45,430
I'm gonna speak up for my mom
at the hearing today.

264
00:12:45,430 --> 00:12:48,130
And how does
your sister feel?

265
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:51,930
Like I'm a traitor.

266
00:12:51,930 --> 00:12:54,230
She's spoken against
my mom's release every year,

267
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:57,440
which is all the board
needs to hear to deny parole.

268
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:59,410
Ugh. That's a tough one.

269
00:12:59,410 --> 00:13:01,880
Yeah.

270
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:13,090
You want me
to come with you today?

271
00:13:13,090 --> 00:13:15,260
Ah, you never know how long
these things are gonna go.

272
00:13:15,260 --> 00:13:20,260
It could be a few hours
before we even get inside.

273
00:13:20,260 --> 00:13:22,260
I'm coming.

274
00:13:24,830 --> 00:13:26,100
[mug clanks]

275
00:13:28,470 --> 00:13:29,500
Chief, you have a call.

276
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,370
It sounds urgent.

277
00:13:31,370 --> 00:13:33,440
Okay, stand by.

278
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,410
Here he is.

279
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:36,010
This is Chief Boden.

280
00:13:36,010 --> 00:13:37,340
I'm in trouble.

281
00:13:37,350 --> 00:13:39,950
Ernie, where are you?

282
00:13:39,950 --> 00:13:42,980
Uncle Ray makes me do it.

283
00:13:42,980 --> 00:13:44,350
I know.

284
00:13:44,350 --> 00:13:47,920
Just tell me where you are.

285
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:50,360
He'd kill me
if he knew I called you.

286
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:53,330
I will not
let that happen.

287
00:13:53,330 --> 00:13:56,560
Ernie, please,
let me help you.

288
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:59,130
Ernie.

289
00:13:59,130 --> 00:14:01,940
Just tell me
where you are.

290
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:04,470
In front of some store

291
00:14:04,470 --> 00:14:06,340
on South Halsted
and Marquette.

292
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:08,540
Okay. Don't move.

293
00:14:08,540 --> 00:14:10,840
I am on my way.

294
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,020
[tires screech]

295
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:30,960
Ernie?

296
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:33,070
Ernie!

297
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:42,310
We take parts of bone
and cartilage from one vertebra

298
00:14:42,310 --> 00:14:44,510
and fuse it onto the next.

299
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:47,010
And then we inject
your own platelets

300
00:14:47,020 --> 00:14:49,980
into the area,
which increases healing.

301
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:52,120
Recovery time
could be four weeks

302
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,950
instead of one year.

303
00:14:57,090 --> 00:14:58,460
How come
I didn't hear about this

304
00:14:58,460 --> 00:15:00,030
from my other surgeon?

305
00:15:00,030 --> 00:15:01,930
This isn't covered
by an H.M.O.

306
00:15:01,930 --> 00:15:02,930
It's experimental.

307
00:15:02,930 --> 00:15:04,630
I'm not gonna lie to you.

308
00:15:04,630 --> 00:15:06,370
There are real risks here,

309
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:09,170
including
partial paralysis.

310
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:16,010
Partial paralysis?

311
00:15:16,010 --> 00:15:18,580
I am so sorry.

312
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:22,150
I, um... I guess I didn't realize
how risky it was.

313
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:24,450
Hey.

314
00:15:26,520 --> 00:15:28,050
If I'm gonna risk anything,

315
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:31,360
I'll risk it on you and me
in Madrid.

316
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:37,660
Is there anyone present
who would like to speak

317
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:40,470
either on behalf of
or in opposition to

318
00:15:40,470 --> 00:15:43,940
Nancy Annalyn Casey's
request for parole?

319
00:15:43,940 --> 00:15:46,140
Yes.

320
00:15:46,140 --> 00:15:48,310
My name is Matthew Casey.

321
00:15:48,310 --> 00:15:53,080
I'm Nancy's son.
I'd like to speak, please.

322
00:15:56,980 --> 00:16:00,020
In four years, you've never
spoken before, Mr. Casey.

323
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:01,150
Why now?

324
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:04,320
What's changed?

325
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:07,060
Well, uh,
when I was seven,

326
00:16:07,060 --> 00:16:11,160
I, uh, I stole a baseball mitt
from a sporting goods store.

327
00:16:11,170 --> 00:16:14,400
I got caught,
and the owner

328
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:17,700
wanted to call the cops,
teach me a lesson.

329
00:16:17,710 --> 00:16:20,310
But my mom came down there
and, uh,

330
00:16:20,310 --> 00:16:22,610
got him to agree
to let me work off

331
00:16:22,610 --> 00:16:25,710
the cost of the mitt
by sweeping his floor.

332
00:16:25,710 --> 00:16:28,310
And when my sister
crashed the family car,

333
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:30,280
my dad wanted
to kick her out of the house.

334
00:16:30,290 --> 00:16:33,120
But my mom talked to him,

335
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:35,220
worked it out
where Christie could work off

336
00:16:35,220 --> 00:16:37,490
the repairs
by cleaning dad's office.

337
00:16:39,530 --> 00:16:43,500
What I'm trying to say is that
my mom understood punishment,

338
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:47,000
but she also
understood forgiveness.

339
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,600
She did a horrible thing

340
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:51,070
that she regrets terribly,

341
00:16:51,070 --> 00:16:53,740
and she's paid the price

342
00:16:53,740 --> 00:16:56,040
with 15 years
of her life.

343
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:59,650
But now it's time
for forgiveness,

344
00:16:59,650 --> 00:17:01,780
from all of us.

345
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:08,350
We lost both our father
and our mother that day.

346
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:16,130
So, uh...
So what's changed?

347
00:17:16,130 --> 00:17:19,730
Well, I have.

348
00:17:19,730 --> 00:17:22,140
I forgive her now.

349
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,810
Okay.

350
00:17:28,810 --> 00:17:30,340
Thank you, Mr. Casey.

351
00:17:30,350 --> 00:17:31,710
Thank you.

352
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:35,350
Would anyone else
like to speak,

353
00:17:35,350 --> 00:17:37,820
either for
or in opposition to

354
00:17:37,820 --> 00:17:41,090
Ms. Casey's possible parole?

355
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,270
All right, then,
Ms. Casey.

356
00:17:59,470 --> 00:18:02,610
We'll start with
a simple question.

357
00:18:02,610 --> 00:18:05,850
Do you feel remorse
for your crime?

358
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:11,320
Yes.

359
00:18:13,850 --> 00:18:17,660
Yes. Yes, I do...

360
00:18:18,590 --> 00:18:20,690
Every day.

361
00:18:39,450 --> 00:18:40,810
Hey, there, fellas.

362
00:18:40,820 --> 00:18:43,550
I'm Brian Zvonecek.

363
00:18:43,550 --> 00:18:46,350
I'm relieving here
for the next couple shifts.

364
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:50,190
[door shuts]

365
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:52,890
[keys clank]

366
00:18:52,890 --> 00:18:54,790
Hey.

367
00:18:57,630 --> 00:19:00,170
I said hey.

368
00:19:06,740 --> 00:19:08,740
I know what you're doing.

369
00:19:08,740 --> 00:19:11,810
Oh, yeah?
What am I doing?

370
00:19:17,150 --> 00:19:18,620
You're not pissed at me

371
00:19:18,620 --> 00:19:20,330
because I didn't tell you first.

372
00:19:20,330 --> 00:19:22,490
You're pissed off because
 you don't want me to go.

373
00:19:26,730 --> 00:19:31,160
Clarice is moving in.
She's gonna need your key.

374
00:19:37,270 --> 00:19:38,570
[chuckles] This guy,

375
00:19:38,570 --> 00:19:42,480
he has a heart attack
coming down the stairs.

376
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:43,840
I mean, his heart stops
and everything.

377
00:19:43,850 --> 00:19:45,240
- I think heard about that.
- Yeah, yeah.

378
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,450
And we had to put
the paddles on him and...

379
00:19:46,450 --> 00:19:48,810
[clicks mouth] he pops
 right back up,

380
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:50,680
like, no big deal,
you know?

381
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:51,820
I mean,
he completed training.

382
00:19:51,820 --> 00:19:53,490
- I think he's over at 94.
- [man laughs]

383
00:19:53,490 --> 00:19:54,820
Gave him the nickname
"Dead Frank."

384
00:19:54,820 --> 00:19:57,190
[laughter]

385
00:19:57,190 --> 00:19:59,190
I know where I heard
that story before.

386
00:19:59,190 --> 00:20:00,790
You're the guy
with the podcast.

387
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,930
We love that podcast.

388
00:20:02,930 --> 00:20:06,630
Herrmann, right?

389
00:20:06,630 --> 00:20:09,340
He put you up to this.

390
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:11,540
No, nobody did.

391
00:20:11,540 --> 00:20:14,810
[alarm chimes]

392
00:20:14,810 --> 00:20:16,840
[over P.A.] Truck 67,
assist the invalid.

393
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:17,980
- Hey, Brian.
- Yeah?

394
00:20:17,980 --> 00:20:20,850
- Why don't you drive?
- Seriously?

395
00:20:20,850 --> 00:20:22,280
Yeah, I'm getting tired of it.

396
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:25,380
Been looking for someone
to take over.

397
00:20:27,490 --> 00:20:30,560
[engine starts]

398
00:20:32,660 --> 00:20:34,560
It's weird
without Otis here.

399
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:35,900
Who am I supposed to jag?

400
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:37,400
Don't look at me.

401
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,760
And Severide's gone too.

402
00:20:38,770 --> 00:20:40,870
I mean, he's as cocky
as they come,

403
00:20:40,870 --> 00:20:42,640
but if you were
lying in the street,

404
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:44,240
he'd give you the shirt
off his back.

405
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,840
If you're
lying in the street,

406
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:47,410
why do you need
his shirt?

407
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:48,710
You know what I mean.

408
00:20:48,710 --> 00:20:50,240
How many times
I gotta tell you to stay out

409
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:51,910
of the first watch crate,
Mouch?

410
00:20:51,910 --> 00:20:54,610
The tempt me with
these marshmallows, Lieutenant.

411
00:20:54,620 --> 00:20:55,780
What am I supposed to do?

412
00:20:55,780 --> 00:20:58,920
Give me one.

413
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:02,760
- Hey.
- Hey.

414
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:04,820
- You hear anything?
- Not yet.

415
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:06,430
It could be a couple days.

416
00:21:06,430 --> 00:21:08,690
Fingers crossed.

417
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:10,300
Thanks.

418
00:21:10,300 --> 00:21:13,270
Chief, maybe we should
rethink the dog, eh?

419
00:21:13,270 --> 00:21:15,300
Time 51 got one.

420
00:21:15,300 --> 00:21:16,740
Plus, it would really
piss off Mouch.

421
00:21:16,740 --> 00:21:18,870
No way.

422
00:21:20,010 --> 00:21:21,770
Peter Mills,
where is that dog?

423
00:21:21,780 --> 00:21:24,940
Um, I found a home for it.

424
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:27,380
- You did?
- Thank God.

425
00:21:27,380 --> 00:21:28,650
[alarm chimes]

426
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:31,020
[over P.A.] Truck 81, ambo 61,
engine 51,

427
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:33,490
78 Racine, apartment fire.

428
00:21:33,490 --> 00:21:35,860
That's Ernie's house.

429
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:44,000
[siren blaring]

430
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:02,880
Ernie?

431
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:09,590
Ernie?

432
00:22:09,590 --> 00:22:11,520
- I'm going up.
- Okay.

433
00:22:11,530 --> 00:22:14,490
Spread out!

434
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,060
Ernie!

435
00:22:17,830 --> 00:22:21,430
Ernie, call out!

436
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:23,700
Ernie!

437
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,650
Ernie!

438
00:22:33,650 --> 00:22:36,550
Ernie, call out.

439
00:22:36,550 --> 00:22:40,690
Ernie! Ernie!

440
00:22:43,660 --> 00:22:45,760
Ernie!

441
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:55,000
Ernie?
Can you hear me?

442
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,040
I'll get you
out of here.

443
00:22:57,040 --> 00:23:01,570
Come on.
Stay with me.

444
00:23:01,580 --> 00:23:04,140
[murmurs, grunts]

445
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:10,050
I'm gonna
get you out of here, Ernie.

446
00:23:15,820 --> 00:23:17,590
[grunting]

447
00:23:19,030 --> 00:23:23,060
Okay, stay with me.
Stay with me.

448
00:23:30,740 --> 00:23:33,010
Shay.

449
00:23:35,710 --> 00:23:38,740
Ernie. Ernie.

450
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:26,120
[dog whimpering]

451
00:25:29,090 --> 00:25:31,960
What is that?

452
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:33,660
I lied.

453
00:25:33,660 --> 00:25:37,760
Uh, I... I couldn't find
anyone to take her.

454
00:25:37,770 --> 00:25:41,200
And I couldn't bring her
to my place.

455
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,640
Sorry, guys.

456
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:46,670
Oh! Come here.

457
00:25:53,610 --> 00:25:57,880
[both murmuring]

458
00:25:57,890 --> 00:26:00,690
[kisses]

459
00:26:00,690 --> 00:26:02,620
[murmuring to puppy]

460
00:26:03,620 --> 00:26:06,830
[whispers] Hey.
Do you wanna say hi to Chief?

461
00:26:06,830 --> 00:26:09,030
[dog whimpering]

462
00:26:09,030 --> 00:26:11,030
[dog licking]

463
00:26:14,570 --> 00:26:17,640
[cell phone ringing]

464
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:21,170
Hello?

465
00:26:21,180 --> 00:26:22,340
Yeah.

466
00:26:22,340 --> 00:26:23,810
[whispers] The parole board.

467
00:26:23,810 --> 00:26:26,680
- I know you like my nose.
- [Casey murmuring]

468
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:28,250
[Casey whispering] Look at that.
What's that?

469
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:29,950
Who's that?

470
00:26:29,950 --> 00:26:32,220
[laughs]

471
00:26:32,220 --> 00:26:35,120
Ahh, jeez.

472
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:36,960
Fine.

473
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:40,160
What are we gonna
call this mutt?

474
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:42,660
- Pouch.
- Huh?

475
00:26:42,660 --> 00:26:44,300
Half pooch, half couch.

476
00:26:44,300 --> 00:26:45,700
[both laugh]

477
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:47,670
Peter Mills,

478
00:26:47,670 --> 00:26:49,900
we're gonna need some bacon.

479
00:26:49,900 --> 00:26:51,040
- Right.
- Thank you.

480
00:26:54,310 --> 00:26:56,210
And?

481
00:26:56,210 --> 00:26:58,380
They granted her parole.

482
00:26:58,380 --> 00:27:00,210
Hey, congratulations.

483
00:27:00,210 --> 00:27:02,180
Yeah.

484
00:27:02,180 --> 00:27:03,980
What?

485
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:05,750
Well, there is one condition.

486
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:09,390
She has to move into
a stable household.

487
00:27:09,390 --> 00:27:12,090
Meaning with me.

488
00:27:12,090 --> 00:27:13,890
Oh.

489
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:16,120
[door closes]

490
00:28:24,360 --> 00:28:27,030
[siren blares]

491
00:28:36,810 --> 00:28:37,840
[tires screeching]

492
00:28:37,850 --> 00:28:39,810
[horn honking]

493
00:28:41,410 --> 00:28:44,780
[siren blaring]

494
00:28:59,470 --> 00:29:01,870
[both grunting]

495
00:29:01,870 --> 00:29:04,170
Come on!
Come on!

496
00:29:04,170 --> 00:29:05,800
[tire iron clatters]

497
00:29:07,370 --> 00:29:08,470
[sirens approaching]

498
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:10,810
A little boy?

499
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:15,410
Step back! We got it.

500
00:29:23,190 --> 00:29:25,860
[truck beeping]

501
00:29:32,370 --> 00:29:35,230
Nice work. [chuckles]

502
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:37,170
These older houses
are a tight squeeze.

503
00:29:37,170 --> 00:29:38,870
Thanks.

504
00:29:38,870 --> 00:29:41,110
You know, I come from
a family of doctors.

505
00:29:41,110 --> 00:29:42,210
But the first time
I saw a firefighter

506
00:29:42,210 --> 00:29:45,210
jump into a truck
and roar off,

507
00:29:45,210 --> 00:29:48,110
man, I knew I wasn't
going to medical school.

508
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:50,820
I wanted to drive
a fire truck.

509
00:29:50,820 --> 00:29:52,080
Your parents
okay with that?

510
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:54,220
Nope, but I am.

511
00:29:54,220 --> 00:29:56,120
[laughs] Good for you.

512
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:58,460
Hey, you know,
this spot in our house

513
00:29:58,460 --> 00:30:00,390
is gonna be permanent.

514
00:30:00,390 --> 00:30:02,160
You should put in
for a transfer.

515
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:04,500
- What, are you serious?
- Hell, yeah.

516
00:30:04,500 --> 00:30:06,500
I've laughed harder this week
than the last two years.

517
00:30:06,500 --> 00:30:08,100
[both chuckle]

518
00:30:08,100 --> 00:30:10,070
You should see this place
in the summertime.

519
00:30:10,070 --> 00:30:12,000
Girls everywhere,

520
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:14,110
all wanting a picture
with Chicago's finest.

521
00:30:14,110 --> 00:30:15,470
[chuckling]

522
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:18,580
It's the best house
in the city.

523
00:30:22,220 --> 00:30:24,250
Public defender
is saying battery,

524
00:30:24,250 --> 00:30:27,350
citing you personally
and the department at large.

525
00:30:27,350 --> 00:30:29,250
If they wanna
have that discussion...

526
00:30:29,260 --> 00:30:32,460
You're having it now.

527
00:30:32,460 --> 00:30:35,130
I apprehended a suspect
in an arson and murder case,

528
00:30:35,130 --> 00:30:36,560
a suspect with an A.P.B.
out on him

529
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:38,130
who the C.P.D. did not
have enough manpower...

530
00:30:38,130 --> 00:30:40,530
Do you wanna go back
and take the cop's test?

531
00:30:40,530 --> 00:30:43,140
Because it's not too late.

532
00:30:51,110 --> 00:30:53,110
- Ah, come on now, Wallace.
- No, no, no.

533
00:30:53,110 --> 00:30:55,250
These are my bugles.

534
00:30:55,250 --> 00:30:56,920
I'm going on furlough.

535
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:58,880
When I get back,
you can tell me

536
00:30:58,890 --> 00:31:00,520
if I should
put 'em back on again.

537
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:02,250
[bugles clattering]

538
00:31:05,890 --> 00:31:07,090
Chief, I just wanna
let you...

539
00:31:07,090 --> 00:31:08,860
Not now.

540
00:31:30,220 --> 00:31:31,450
[car door closes]

541
00:31:31,450 --> 00:31:34,890
I'm a stupid ass.
I know.

542
00:31:34,890 --> 00:31:36,190
Yup.

543
00:31:39,260 --> 00:31:42,590
And I'm sorry.
I should've...

544
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:44,600
I should've camped outside
your room

545
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:48,170
to tell you first.

546
00:31:48,170 --> 00:31:50,640
You're my best friend, Shay.

547
00:31:54,570 --> 00:31:57,640
Next time...

548
00:31:59,110 --> 00:32:00,550
- Hey.
- [Shay laughs]

549
00:32:00,550 --> 00:32:03,250
No next time,
I swear.

550
00:32:03,250 --> 00:32:05,550
I'm glad you're
getting yourself healthy,

551
00:32:05,550 --> 00:32:08,420
even if it means
I have to let you go.

552
00:32:10,190 --> 00:32:12,390
No one's letting go.

553
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:17,230
Come on, let's go in.

554
00:32:17,230 --> 00:32:19,230
- I'm cold.
- All right, yeah.

555
00:32:21,570 --> 00:32:24,140
Hey, you know, tasers
are totally against the rules.

556
00:32:24,140 --> 00:32:26,540
Yeah, I know that.
It's page one.

557
00:32:26,540 --> 00:32:29,040
All you.

558
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:31,240
[all] Surprise!

559
00:32:31,250 --> 00:32:33,250
[cheers and applause]

560
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:36,080
You...

561
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:38,320
- Hey.
- Hi.

562
00:32:40,020 --> 00:32:42,720
I'm not sure what
we're gonna do without you.

563
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,160
- [Severide exhales]
- Cheers.

564
00:32:46,160 --> 00:32:49,960
[background chatter, laughter]

565
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:51,160
Hey.

566
00:32:51,170 --> 00:32:54,100
Look, I promise you
that I understand,

567
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:55,400
you know, this is just
an opportunity

568
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,070
for us to be roommates.

569
00:32:57,070 --> 00:33:00,240
Nothing more...

570
00:33:07,110 --> 00:33:10,080
What was that?

571
00:33:10,080 --> 00:33:11,480
I love you.

572
00:33:11,490 --> 00:33:14,250
I've always loved you.

573
00:33:14,250 --> 00:33:17,020
I love you too.

574
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:31,300
You sure you wanna do this,
Peter Mills?

575
00:33:31,310 --> 00:33:33,170
I've been waiting
 all day, baby.

576
00:33:33,170 --> 00:33:34,640
Wanna sneak out of here?

577
00:33:34,640 --> 00:33:37,180
Your place, ten minutes?

578
00:33:37,180 --> 00:33:38,340
You're on.

579
00:33:38,350 --> 00:33:40,310
Mm...

580
00:33:47,620 --> 00:33:49,720
[laughter]

581
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:51,520
- Kick flips?
- No, you.

582
00:33:51,530 --> 00:33:52,760
No, you.

583
00:33:55,460 --> 00:33:57,460
I'm telling you, guys,
it wasn't that bad.

584
00:33:57,460 --> 00:34:02,230
[audio muffled, fading]

585
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:18,750
Sorry.
Have you seen Kelly?

586
00:34:18,750 --> 00:34:21,650
Yeah, he's over there.

587
00:34:21,660 --> 00:34:24,420
- Or, was...
- Oh.

588
00:34:34,370 --> 00:34:36,270
[engine turns off]

589
00:34:43,210 --> 00:34:46,780
[distant laughter]

590
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,750
So it's 15 degrees,
and there was

591
00:34:50,750 --> 00:34:52,420
this homeless guy
that used to hang around

592
00:34:52,420 --> 00:34:53,690
in an alley
behind the house.

593
00:34:53,690 --> 00:34:56,350
And we find him,
and he is frozen solid.

594
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:58,390
I mean,
he's a block of ice.

595
00:34:58,390 --> 00:35:00,590
So I call the morgue
and I say, "Listen.

596
00:35:00,590 --> 00:35:02,090
We got a frozen dead guy,
and you gotta

597
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:03,730
come and pick him up."

598
00:35:03,730 --> 00:35:06,230
And they say,
"Well, he can't just be dead.

599
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:09,270
He's gotta be warm and dead
before we'll come and get him."

600
00:35:09,270 --> 00:35:12,140
So we dragged the homeless guy
across to the apparatus floor,

601
00:35:12,140 --> 00:35:13,470
and we wait for him
to thaw out,

602
00:35:13,470 --> 00:35:14,570
for about ten hours.

603
00:35:14,580 --> 00:35:16,710
Anyway, eventually
he got warm enough

604
00:35:16,710 --> 00:35:18,740
and dead enough
to actually be dead,

605
00:35:18,750 --> 00:35:20,250
so they came and got him.

606
00:35:20,250 --> 00:35:24,320
You still telling
that one?

607
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:29,650
Well, I'll be damned.

608
00:35:29,660 --> 00:35:30,760
- Guys.
- Hey.

609
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:33,790
- How you doing?
- Dad.

610
00:35:35,530 --> 00:35:37,230
- You want something to eat?
- Oh, nah.

611
00:35:37,230 --> 00:35:40,500
I'm good, thanks.

612
00:35:43,770 --> 00:35:47,240
Uh... [deep breath]

613
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:50,280
I'm leaving the C.F.D.

614
00:35:54,580 --> 00:35:56,280
What happens when
you and this Renee

615
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:58,880
get tired of each other,
and you find yourself

616
00:35:58,890 --> 00:36:01,190
in some godforsaken country
with nothing to show for it

617
00:36:01,190 --> 00:36:02,750
- but a pension?
- I don't know.

618
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:04,820
This doesn't look so bad.

619
00:36:04,830 --> 00:36:06,220
Trust me.

620
00:36:06,230 --> 00:36:08,290
You're worried about
partial paralysis?

621
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:09,830
How about full paralysis?

622
00:36:09,830 --> 00:36:12,900
'Cause that's what this is.

623
00:36:15,770 --> 00:36:19,240
There is no replacing
rescue squad...

624
00:36:26,750 --> 00:36:30,180
But you already know that.

625
00:36:30,180 --> 00:36:31,750
That's why
you came out here,

626
00:36:31,750 --> 00:36:34,890
so I could talk you
out of going.

627
00:36:39,230 --> 00:36:42,830
Look. I know I wasn't
there for you

628
00:36:42,830 --> 00:36:44,930
like I could've been
or should've been,

629
00:36:44,930 --> 00:36:47,630
and I'm three wives
removed from your mother

630
00:36:47,630 --> 00:36:51,300
and I'm in no position
to give you advice.

631
00:36:51,310 --> 00:36:52,740
But you're scared, Kelly.

632
00:36:52,740 --> 00:36:55,810
And you know
why you're scared?

633
00:36:55,810 --> 00:36:59,240
'Cause you're not ready
for this.

634
00:36:59,250 --> 00:37:02,910
Bennie, you ready?

635
00:37:08,420 --> 00:37:10,960
She's counting on me.
I promised her.

636
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:13,860
She'll get over it.

637
00:37:13,860 --> 00:37:17,960
Disappoint anyone...
Hell, disappoint everyone,

638
00:37:17,970 --> 00:37:22,230
but don't ever
disappoint yourself.

639
00:37:24,970 --> 00:37:28,710
It's good to see you.

640
00:37:28,710 --> 00:37:30,840
You too, pop.

641
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:51,360
[background chatter]

642
00:37:51,370 --> 00:37:54,900
[distant siren]

643
00:38:13,290 --> 00:38:15,750
Hey.

644
00:38:15,760 --> 00:38:19,290
What's going on?

645
00:38:19,290 --> 00:38:22,060
I'm, uh...

646
00:38:22,060 --> 00:38:24,930
I'm gonna get the surgery.

647
00:38:24,930 --> 00:38:27,300
Oh, Kelly, come on.

648
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:29,870
It's... It's just not
worth the risk.

649
00:38:29,870 --> 00:38:32,670
I mean,
we'll do it right.

650
00:38:32,670 --> 00:38:33,840
You'll come with me.

651
00:38:33,840 --> 00:38:36,040
You'll recuperate
in Madr...

652
00:38:40,380 --> 00:38:43,450
You wanna stay.

653
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:00,030
I should've known. [chuckles]

654
00:39:00,030 --> 00:39:03,840
I was that close
to not even telling you.

655
00:39:06,970 --> 00:39:08,940
And you would've
come with me to Madrid.

656
00:39:08,940 --> 00:39:12,840
And... the sky would've
been the limit for us.

657
00:39:12,850 --> 00:39:15,950
Hey, hey.

658
00:39:15,950 --> 00:39:20,750
What you did might be
the most important thing

659
00:39:20,750 --> 00:39:23,820
anyone's ever done for me.

660
00:39:28,090 --> 00:39:31,360
Thank you.

661
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:42,110
Well, uh...
I guess now we're even.

662
00:39:44,580 --> 00:39:48,010
Yeah. We're even.

663
00:40:24,920 --> 00:40:27,190
[knock at door]

664
00:40:33,130 --> 00:40:34,690
Shonda.

665
00:40:34,690 --> 00:40:37,500
Wallace.

666
00:40:37,500 --> 00:40:39,830
Can I please see Jimmy?

667
00:40:39,830 --> 00:40:41,900
No.

668
00:40:41,900 --> 00:40:44,170
- He's not your son.
- The hell he ain't.

669
00:40:44,170 --> 00:40:47,710
I raised him
from the time he was three.

670
00:40:47,710 --> 00:40:49,710
Never used the word
"stepson."

671
00:40:49,710 --> 00:40:52,540
Not once.

672
00:40:53,850 --> 00:40:56,480
I need to see him.

673
00:41:04,020 --> 00:41:06,090
[dog barks]

674
00:41:06,090 --> 00:41:09,590
Hey. Ralphie.

675
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:12,630
How are you?
I miss you, boy.

676
00:41:19,140 --> 00:41:21,570
Dad.

677
00:41:28,810 --> 00:41:32,750
[murmurs emotionally]

678
00:41:52,140 --> 00:41:54,010
[tap on glass]

679
00:42:01,850 --> 00:42:04,550
You ready?

